    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/tooling-sap-build-blog-posts/joule-studio-how-to-create-document-grounding/bc-p/14345838#M76</id>
    <title>Re: Joule Studio: How to Create Document Grounding</title>
    <updated>2026-03-10T18:41:30.062000+01:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Dan_Wroblewski</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/72</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;&lt;a href="https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/2236509"&gt;@Abhishek_Anand32&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;This is beyond the scope of this blog, since the destination should point to whatever document store you want to use. But I will look into this in the next week and write separately about this.&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/tooling-sap-build-blog-posts/joule-studio-how-to-create-document-grounding/bc-p/14345838#M76"/>
    <published>2026-03-10T18:41:30.062000+01:00</published>
  </entry>
  <entry>
    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/tooling-sap-build-blog-posts/joule-studio-how-to-create-document-grounding/bc-p/14345840#M77</id>
    <title>Re: Joule Studio: How to Create Document Grounding</title>
    <updated>2026-03-10T18:44:14.414000+01:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Dan_Wroblewski</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/72</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;&lt;a href="https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/2286540"&gt;@Julia_Kraus16&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;Are you asking or telling me about pipelines, or has there been a change I wasn't aware of?&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;With this method of creating document grounding, all you need to supply is a destination to an AI Core and to a Document Store. SAP Build (Joule Studio) will handle:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;UL&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Creating the Resource Group&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Adding the Generic Secret (include all that Base64 stuff)&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Create a pipeline for the documents in your Document Store&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&lt;P&gt;All the stuff you have to do for document grounding in AI Core, still needs to be done but Joule Studio will do it for you. Of course, currently you cannot reuse an existing pipeline you created manually, but I am told that is coming.&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/tooling-sap-build-blog-posts/joule-studio-how-to-create-document-grounding/bc-p/14345840#M77"/>
    <published>2026-03-10T18:44:14.414000+01:00</published>
  </entry>
  <entry>
    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/tooling-sap-build-blog-posts/joule-studio-how-to-create-document-grounding/bc-p/14345843#M78</id>
    <title>Re: Joule Studio: How to Create Document Grounding</title>
    <updated>2026-03-10T18:47:28.257000+01:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Dan_Wroblewski</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/72</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;&lt;a href="https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/2279887"&gt;@nicholas_nicolis&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;I am sorry I missed your question from a while ago. I am assuming you created a Document Grounding in the Control Tower but your agent is not able to get information from it.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;First, it's important to make sure agent is built the best it can be so that it always recognizes when to use the Document Grounding tool you added.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Second, assuming the first is OK, sometimes Document Grounding has not worked for me. To be honest, I haven't found a good answer for that. I often reload the project, stop and restart the testing, and it will eventually work, but I'm not sure what is going on.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Third, you must consider that something is wrong with AI Core, which has had some periods of instability over the last month.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/tooling-sap-build-blog-posts/joule-studio-how-to-create-document-grounding/bc-p/14345843#M78"/>
    <published>2026-03-10T18:47:28.257000+01:00</published>
  </entry>
