    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;I ran Identity Provision, and was able to provision users into Work Zone, Advanced. But I made a mistake and I want to remove certain users. How do I do this?&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;I tried by filtering the source (and target) to only recognize users whose last name was "Wroblewski", which seems to have worked since in the logs it shows only 2 users read. And I also added the property&amp;nbsp;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;ips.delete.existedbefore.entities&lt;/STRONG&gt; and set to true, and I thought this would remove all but "Wroblewski" users. But it did not work.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Also, can't I add the users to groups in IAS and then just provision the groups into Work Zone?&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;a href="https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/5121"&gt;@Yumnahabbasi&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/5128"&gt;@florian_buech&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/tooling-sap-build-forum/how-to-remove-ias-users-from-work-zone-advanced/td-p/14347174"/>
