      <name>Dan_Wroblewski</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/72</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;&lt;a href="https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/1504836"&gt;@KodyZhang&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;Yes. Joule Studio does nothing more than create resource group, generic secret to the document store, and then a pipeline. If you need some sort of orchestration or filtering or whatever, then you have to do it via code. But note that at the moment you cannot import a pipeline created in AICore manually or via code into a Joule Studio project.&lt;/P&gt;</content>
